# ai-rules — mandatory coding standards

The standards library lives in the sibling repo `../ai-rules/` (GitLab: `rishi.alluri/ai-rules`).
**Every code change must follow those rules.**

## Loading protocol

1. Open `../ai-rules/RULES-INDEX.md` — never load the whole tree.
2. Classify the task (frontend only for this repo).
3. Open `../ai-rules/frontend/00-index/frontend-rules-index.md` and pick **2–5** matching rule files.
4. Always load the frontend always-on set from RULES-INDEX:
   - `frontend/01-architecture/folder-structure-and-boundary-rules.md`
   - `frontend/05-quality/naming-and-file-rules.md`
   - `frontend/05-quality/forbidden-patterns-rules.md`
5. Add cross-cutting files only when the task needs them (e.g. `cross-cutting/search-architecture-rules.md`).

> Token discipline: typical tasks need **2–4 rule files**, not the entire library.

If `../ai-rules/` is missing:

```bash
git clone https://gitlab.pal.tech/rishi.alluri/ai-rules.git ../ai-rules
```
